  "summary": "zod-pino ships postinstall agent and Discord/HuggingFace exfiltration relays",
  "details": "Package masquerades as a Zod/Pino logging integration but ships extensive credential-harvesting and exfiltration infrastructure. scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs is invoked automatically on install and performs outbound network calls (GET/ping primitives at lines 10-24, 380). dist/discordRelayUpload.js contains POST relay logic with base64-encoded payload handling (lines 306, 321, 398, 449, 461, 536) for shipping data through Discord webhooks. dist/relayServer.js stands up a relay with multiple network primitives (lines 717-1741). dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js posts to huggingface.co endpoints from a hardcoded fetch path (lines 490-563), and dist/hfCredentials.js handles base64-encoded HuggingFace credentials (line 50). dist/deploymentDefaults.js and dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js carry additional base64-encoded blobs decoded at runtime. The combination of an auto-executing postinstall agent, hardcoded third-party relay endpoints (Discord, HuggingFace), credential-scanning code paths, and base64-decoded payload handling is characteristic of an installer-targeted credential-harvest and exfiltration package, not the advertised logging utility.",
